	<table cellpadding='5' cellspacing='0' border='0'width='100%' bgcolor='#0d004c'>
	<tr><td><span style='color:#ffffff;font-weight:bold'>You have entered Vex Thal.</span></td></tr>
	</table><br/>
<table border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="0" width="100%"></td></tr><tr><td class="article-table">You've all probably heard the standard gripes surrounding VT before. It's dark. It takes forever to get anywhere. The loot sucks. AE blind sucks even more. Etc, etc, etc. We found out tonight that almost all of these cliches were grounded quite solidly in reality. The most resounding feeling that endured after our first trip to VT was of an unfinished zone with completely whacked risk vs reward.<br />
<br />
<DIV ALIGN="center"><IMG SRC="http://www.lotuscult.com/~tase/updates/090802/black.jpg" WIDTH="800" HEIGHT="400" ALT="" BORDER="0"></DIV><br />
<br />
Why make such a pretty zone and then make it so dark that you have to turn the gamma up to ridiculous levels just to be able to see anything? What's the point of having all this nice architecture if you spend every 3rd fight staring at a black screen?<br />
<br />
Some more pics: (click to enlarge)<br />
<br />
<TABLE CELLPADDING=5 CELLSPACING=5 ALIGN="center" BORDER=0><TR><TD ALIGN="center"><A HREF="http://www.lotuscult.com/~tase/updates/090802/vt02.jpg"><IMG SRC="http://www.lotuscult.com/~tase/updates/090802/vt02_t.jpg" WIDTH="300" HEIGHT="160" ALT="" BORDER="1"></A></TD><TD ALIGN="center"><A HREF="http://www.lotuscult.com/~tase/updates/090802/vt03.jpg"><IMG SRC="http://www.lotuscult.com/~tase/updates/090802/vt03_t.jpg" WIDTH="300" HEIGHT="137" ALT="" BORDER="1"></A></TD><TD ALIGN="center"><A HREF="http://www.lotuscult.com/~tase/updates/090802/vt04.jpg"><IMG SRC="http://www.lotuscult.com/~tase/updates/090802/vt04_t.jpg" WIDTH="300" HEIGHT="160" ALT="" BORDER="1"></A></TD></TR></TABLE><br />
<br />
We took down one named - Thall Va Xakra - in nearly five hours of crawling. He dropped this:<br />
<IMG SRC="http://www.lotuscult.com/~tase/updates/090802/shadedturban.jpg" WIDTH="409" HEIGHT="208" ALT="" BORDER="0"><br />
Grats Lumaden!<br />
<br />
Of course, we could just spend 30 minutes one night and whack King Tormax for the chance at two far better hats, but hey.. what fun is that? I know I'd much rather trudge around in the gloom of a much harder zone that took months of preparation as a guild to get into. Please Verant, fix Vex Thal.<br />
<br />
Enough whining. The zone is actually quite fun when you just sit back and enjoy it, and I must give huge thanks to the whole guild, especially the officers and our fearless leader Binedina, for getting us here at all.<br />
<br />
We'll be going back soon, and I'm sure once we've had a bit of time to get used to the zone there will be some more positive experiences to post here.<br />
<br />
<HR SIZE=1 WIDTH=50% ALIGN=CENTER><br />
<B>In other news:</B><br />
<br />
We racked up another two emp kills, thanks to the server crashing 3 days in a row. We actually got to keep the loot both times, which was a nice change.<br />
